LANE SMOKE TEST
===============

Script: scripts/routing_smoke.py
Purpose: Stress-test pipeline routing across chat, research, and all make lanes
         using a small fast model. Tests wiring and routing — not output quality.


QUICK START
-----------

    cd ~/Oathweaver
    source .venv/bin/activate

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode chat
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode research
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode make --make-type blog
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --all


ALL OPTIONS
-----------

--mode chat
    Runs a single prompt through the chat/conversation lane.
    Uses conversation_reply() directly — no routing gate involved.

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode chat

--mode research
    Runs a single prompt through the full research pipeline
    (foraging → synthesis). Uses force_research=True.

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode research

--mode make --make-type <TYPE>
    Runs a single prompt through a specific make lane.
    Uses force_make=True with the given type_id as the delivery target.
    Each type has a canned prompt built in — override with --prompt.

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode make --make-type blog
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode make --make-type tool
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode make --make-type email
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode make --make-type tool --prompt "write a script that counts files"

--all
    Runs chat + research + every make type sequentially.
    Prints a live one-liner per lane as it finishes, then a summary table.
    Exits 1 if any lane failed.

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --all
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --all --model phi4-mini:3.8b
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --all --prompt "write something short about coffee"

--model <MODEL>
    Ollama model to use for all layers. Defaults to qwen3:4b.
    Any small model available in Ollama works here.

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode chat --model phi4-mini:3.8b
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --all --model gemma3:4b

--prompt <TEXT>
    Override the default canned prompt for the selected lane or type.
    In --all mode, applies the same prompt to every lane.

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode research --prompt "what causes inflation?"
    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --mode make --make-type newsletter --prompt "write about AI trends"

--list-types
    Print all available make type IDs grouped by lane, then exit.

    python scripts/routing_smoke.py --list-types


MAKE TYPE IDS
-------------

Lane: make_content
    blog              Blog Post
    email             Email
    social_post       Social Post

Lane: make_creative
    book_chapter      Book Chapter
    memoir_chapter    Memoir Chapter
    novel_chapter     Novel Chapter
    screenplay        Screenplay

Lane: make_desktop_app
    desktop_app       Desktop App

Lane: make_longform
    essay_long        Long-Form Essay
    essay_short       Short-Form Essay
    guide             Guide
    newsletter        Newsletter
    press_release     Press Release
    tutorial          Tutorial
    video_script      Video Script

Lane: make_specialist
    finance           Financial Analysis
    game_design_doc   Game Design Doc
    history           Historical Essay
    medical           Medical Report
    sports            Sports Analysis

Lane: make_tool
    tool              Tool / Script

Lane: make_app
    web_app           Web App


HOW IT WORKS
------------

The script patches load_model_routing() in-process before the Orchestrator
boots, replacing the real routing config with a minimal version that points
every layer at the chosen small model (2k context, 1 retry, no premium gates,
no reflection loops, research pool parallelism = 1).

No config files are modified. The real model_routing.json is never touched.

In --all mode, each lane gets a fresh Orchestrator instance so state does
not bleed between runs.


OUTPUT
------

Single lane (--mode): verbose stage trace with elapsed times, then result.
On failure, the full exception message and traceback are printed showing the
exact function and file that raised.

    [  0.3s] lane_routed                    Pipeline: make_content | mode=write
    [  2.1s] make_content_draft             ...

    PASS  4.7s  Pipeline: make_content | mode=write

    --- on failure ---

    FAIL  0.3s

    ERROR: unable to load model: qwen3:4b

    --- Traceback ---
    Traceback (most recent call last):
      File "/home/sc/Oathweaver/scripts/routing_smoke.py", line 200, in run_one
        reply = runner(orch, prompt, on_progress)
      File "/home/sc/Oathweaver/SourceCode/orchestrator/main.py", line 4511, in handle_message
        ...
    RuntimeError: unable to load model: qwen3:4b

--all mode: one live line per lane as it finishes, then a summary table.
Failed lanes print their full error message and traceback after the table.

    ✓  chat                            2.1s
    ✓  research                        18.4s
    ✓  make:blog (Blog Post)           6.2s
    ✗  make:web_app (Web App)          0.3s

